{"id":2294,"date":"2020-03-04T13:14:01","date_gmt":"2020-03-04T13:14:01","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/?p=2294"},"modified":"2020-03-04T13:14:02","modified_gmt":"2020-03-04T13:14:02","slug":"egauge-core-key-features","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/tools\/egauge-core-key-features\/","title":{"rendered":"EGAUGE CORE KEY FEATURES"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>By Ruth Carol Atieno<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Why use the <strong>eGauge Core<\/strong> instead of a Killowatt meter? <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>eGauge<\/strong> is a CT meter meaning it measures the power of individual circuits in an electric panel using sensors called current transformers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>eGauge Core<\/strong> is a flexible and very accurate device used when monitoring multiple circuits in any commercial or residential energy monitoring application. Measuring panels of up to 3-phase 277\/480VAC and 6900A.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"http:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG_4945-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2297 lazyload\" width=\"303\" height=\"227\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG_4945-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG_4945-300x225.jpg 300w, https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG_4945-768x576.jpg 768w, https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG_4945-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG_4945-2048x1536.jpg 2048w, https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG_4945-scaled.jpg 1333w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 303px) 100vw, 303px\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 303px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 303\/227;\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This device is a 15 channel energy meter with a 0.5% revenue grade accuracy compliance.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"http:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG_4943-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2296 lazyload\" width=\"309\" height=\"232\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG_4943-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG_4943-300x225.jpg 300w, https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG_4943-768x576.jpg 768w, https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG_4943-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG_4943-2048x1536.jpg 2048w, https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG_4943-scaled.jpg 1333w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 309px) 100vw, 309px\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 309px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 309\/232;\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>eGauge Core<\/strong> has an Ethernet port which allows for access of data from wherever you are in the world. No need to be physically in touch with the device. (<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"www.egauge.net (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"http:\/\/www.egauge.net\" target=\"_blank\">www.egauge.net<\/a>)<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>eGauge<\/strong> also has two USB ports that allows for other options such us the use of WiFi connection.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" data-src=\"http:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG_4944-1024x768.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2303 lazyload\" width=\"312\" height=\"234\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG_4944-1024x768.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG_4944-300x225.jpg 300w, https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG_4944-768x576.jpg 768w, https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG_4944-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG_4944-2048x1536.jpg 2048w, https:\/\/energyzedworld.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/IMG_4944-scaled.jpg 1333w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 312px) 100vw, 312px\" src=\"data:image\/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB3aWR0aD0iMSIgaGVpZ2h0PSIxIiB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciPjwvc3ZnPg==\" style=\"--smush-placeholder-width: 312px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 312\/234;\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The meter will display the energy data collected on a web page in real-time. you will be able to witness the changes in trends every minute or second. It will reveal issues that a normal utility bill meter would not detect.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>While carrying on with your daily life activities,  the <strong>eGauge<\/strong> will keep watch on any abnormal patterns and you will be able to receive mobile alerts. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>eGauge<\/strong> will help you meet your expectations on energy efficiency projects. This metering system has no subscription fee. Eventually, you will save energy and money!!!<\/p>\n<div class=\"energ-after-content\" id=\"energ-1744917425\"><script async src=\"\/\/pagead2.googlesyndication.com\/pagead\/js\/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-4467099352079704\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\"><\/script><ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" style=\"display:inline-block;width:728px;height:90px;\" \ndata-ad-client=\"ca-pub-4467099352079704\" \ndata-ad-slot=\"8891238828\"><\/ins> \n<script> \n(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); \n<\/script>\n<\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>By Ruth Carol Atieno Why use the eGauge Core instead of a Killowatt meter? The eGauge is